member.name: T:GoogleMapsClient.PlaceAutocompletePredictionAPIArgs
member.summary: Arguments used for retrieving place auto-complete predictions

member.name: P:GoogleMapsClient.PlaceAutocompletePredictionAPIArgs.Input
member.summary: The text string on which to search. The Place Autocomplete service will return candidate matches based on this string and order results based on their perceived relevance.

member.name: P:GoogleMapsClient.PlaceAutocompletePredictionAPIArgs.Radius
member.summary: Defines the distance (in meters) within which to return place results. You may bias results to a specified circle by passing a location and a radius parameter. Doing so instructs the Places service to prefer showing results within that circle; results outside of the defined area may still be displayed.

member.name: P:GoogleMapsClient.PlaceAutocompletePredictionAPIArgs.Components
member.summary: A grouping of places to which you would like to restrict your results. Currently, you can use components to filter by up to 5 countries. Countries must be passed as a two character, ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 compatible country code. For example: components=country:fr would restrict your results to places within France. Multiple countries must be passed as multiple country:XX filters, with the pipe character | as a separator.
member.example: For example: components=country:us|country:pr|country:vi|country:gu|country:mp would restrict your results to places within the United States and its unincorporated organized territories.

member.name: P:GoogleMapsClient.PlaceAutocompletePredictionAPIArgs.Language
member.summary: The language in which to return results.

member.name: P:GoogleMapsClient.PlaceAutocompletePredictionAPIArgs.Offset
member.summary: The position, in the input term, of the last character that the service uses to match predictions.
member.example: For example, if the input is Google and the offset is 3, the service will match on Goo. The string determined by the offset is matched against the first word in the input term only. For example, if the input term is Google abc and the offset is 3, the service will attempt to match against Goo abc. If no offset is supplied, the service will use the whole term. The offset should generally be set to the position of the text caret.

member.name: P:GoogleMapsClient.PlaceAutocompletePredictionAPIArgs.Origin
member.summary: The origin point from which to calculate straight-line distance to the destination (returned as distance_meters). If this value is omitted, straight-line distance will not be returned. Must be specified as latitude,longitude.

member.name: P:GoogleMapsClient.PlaceAutocompletePredictionAPIArgs.Region
member.summary: The region code, specified as a ccTLD ("top-level domain") two-character value. Most ccTLD codes are identical to ISO 3166-1 codes, with some notable exceptions.

member.name: P:GoogleMapsClient.PlaceAutocompletePredictionAPIArgs.SessionToken
member.summary: A random string which identifies an autocomplete session for billing purposes.

member.name: P:GoogleMapsClient.PlaceAutocompletePredictionAPIArgs.StrictBounds
member.summary: Returns only those places that are strictly within the region defined by location and radius. This is a restriction, rather than a bias, meaning that results outside this region will not be returned even if they match the user input.

member.name: P:GoogleMapsClient.PlaceDetailAPIArgs.PlaceId
